The paper discusses the development of an automated test generation approach for autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach utilizes Rapidly-exploring Random Trees, which is a common algorithm used in robotics motion planning. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a cost function to guide the test generation, which involves artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the importance of understanding boundary case scenarios, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
